UNIV. OF GEORGIA
HERBARIUM
157385
Specimen Examined for
Georgia Atlas Project
9 November 2005

STEPHENS COUNTY, GEORGIA
*Galax urceolata* (Poiret) Brummitt
[*G. aphylla* L.]

About ¾ mi from mouth of Panther Creek.
Steep slope, E bank of a tributary. Rich
woods. With *Kalmia*, *Rhododendron*, *Magnolia*,
*Tsuga*. Corollas white. Anthers yellow.

Mark A. Garland 126         22 May 1983
The University of Georgia        Athens, GA, U.S.A.

IMAGED 2013
